comments: Allen (BKN) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Randle's (NYK) arm and body that affects his play at the basket.
Knox (NYK) makes marginal contact with Dinwiddie's (BKN) arm that does not prevent him from gathering and passing the ball.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Allen (BKN) is last to touch the ball before it goes out of play.
Randle (NYK) sets the pick in Dinwiddie's (BKN) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Randle (NYK) takes fewer than three steps before releasing his dribble, and he maintains his dribble as he goes to the ground.
Allen (BKN) maintains a legal guarding position on Randle (NYK) during the drive and the two make incidental foot contact.
Ellington (NYK) establishes his left foot as his pivot foot and he maintains his pivot foot before releasing the pass.
Allen (BKN) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Barrett (NYK) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Knox II (NYK) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Irving (BKN) after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Morris (NYK) is firming up in a legal picking position in Dinwiddie's (BKN) path when contact occurs and he absorbs the contact.
Morris (NYK) extends his right hip and does not give Dinwiddie (BKN) the opportunity to avoid the contact.  Dinwiddie is then not in a legal guarding position when he contacts Barrett (NYK).
Randle (NYK) and Allen (BKN) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Irving (BKN) takes fewer than three steps after he has gathered the ball.
Harris (BKN) and Ellington (NYK) briefly engage and separate on the perimeter.
Allen (BKN) makes marginal contact with Randle's (NYK) body during the drive.
Dinwiddie (BKN) sets the screen in Barrett's (NYK) path and does not prevent him from disengaging from the contact.
During the screen, Barrett (NYK) briefly engages Dinwiddie (BKN) before the two disengage and the contact is marginal.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Randle (NYK) is last to touch the ball before it goes out of play.
Knox II (NYK) commits a take foul on Dinwiddie (BKN).
Randle (NYK) sets the screen in Harris's (BKN) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Ellington (NYK) slides his pivot foot before releasing his dribble.
Allen (BKN) moves laterally into Ellington's (NYK) path at the start of the drive and the contact affects his SQBR.
